Description.SourceString: An adorable rabbit! Something about it seems a little weird, though.
What’s its head doing? What is that sound they’re making? That can’t be right.
Maybe it’s time to start running.
Oh no. No no no. No NO NO NO
A seemingly trustworthy rabbit. This one seems vegan, at least.
A phone, mostly used to watch a popular web series.
Science Girl’s faithful sidekick.
A brilliant codebreaker, hounded by a series of numbers he couldn’t quite crack.
It may not be worth as much as some first issues, but it means a lot to Claudette.
The ambulance they took Sally in never made it to the hospital, and she was assumed dead.
The Bleed did things to the flora and fauna that Talbot would spend the rest of his life trying to understand.
A pocketwatch that belonged in life  to another nurse at Crotus Prenn.
Claudette’s logo for her childhood alter ego: Science Girl.
A room for a patient of Crotus Prenn, intended to keep them safe from themselves.
Evidence that the Observer was once, in fact, here.
If its beauty isn’t heartstopping enough, the poison within it certainly is.
A fluffle is a group of rabbits. Sometimes seeing a fluffle means it’s time to run.
His scribbles and scratchings speak to a brilliant mind that began to lose grip on reality.
A scraping from the Tree of Death. The smell permeates even thick glass.
The easiest way to learn if the water is safe is to find out, conclusively, that it isn’t.
A mortifying carnival ride clearly inspired by a designer’s nightmares.
A corn husk doll made to conceal a hidden blade.
He followed a lead to North Africa to learn of a curious new lifeform.
Surrounded by some of humanity’s most depraved members, he reflected on the human condition.
Confronted with this terrifying thing called the Bleed, he steeled his nerves and went in.
Surrounded by bizarre and surreal blue and purple vines, he approached the situation the only way he knew how. Like a chemist.
In the Bleed, something within him changed.
He was a professional codebreaker for the Agency, an elite puzzle-solver.
His superiors didn't like how close he was getting to the truth.
One name didn't fit the list he decoded: among billionaires and corporations, a high school teacher.
The teacher led him deeper down the rabbit hole.
He, and only he, could root out the corruption that went all the way to the top.
Thankfully, they haven't started killing on land. Yet.
The Scout Regiment handled the most dangerous tasks in the fight against the Titans.
Only the best and brightest were invited to apply to this branch of the military.
Their duty was to maintain order inside the Walls.
The Cadet Corps did its best to give new soldiers the tools they needed to survive.
Nobody could have expected what they’d see when a hole was punched in the wall.
